node.text: A recent poll found over 60 percent of people making under $50,000 a year support our reconciliation bill. Why? Because whether you are a working class Republican, Democrat, or Independent, at the end of the day, you want the federal government to finally respond to your needs.

node.title: Working class people understand the need for a decent-paying job.

node.text:
Since the start of the pandemic, billionaires in this country have gotten some $1.8 trillion richer, while half our people live paycheck to paycheck.

Please do not tell me that the billionaires of this country cannot afford to finally pay their fair share of taxes.

node.title: It's time for billionaires to pay their fair share.

node.text: At a time of massive wealth and income inequality and when half our people are living paycheck to paycheck, what the reconciliation bill will finally do is address the needs of our working families by asking the wealthy and large corporations to pay their fair share of taxes.

node.title: This is the most consequential legislation since the 1930s

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Bernie Sanders on September 01, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Abortion is health care. Bernie'.

node.text:
In case a few Supreme Court justices and politicians in Texas forgot, abortion is a constitutional right in this country.

Women in Texas or in any other state must be able to make reproductive health decisions without interference from the government — period.

node.text: A recent poll found over 60 percent of people making under $50,000 a year support our reconciliation bill. Why? Because whether you are a working class Republican, Democrat, or Independent, at the end of the day, you want the federal government to finally respond to your needs.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Bernie Sanders on August 31, 2021. May be a Twitter screenshot of text that says 'Bernie Sanders @BernieSanders The immense devastation caused in Louisiana and in Mississippi by Hurricane Ida will become our new normal unless we get our act together and take bold action to combat climate change NOW.'.
Photo by Bernie Sanders in Cedar Rapids, Iowa. May be an image of one or more people, people standing and outdoors.

node.text: Thank you to the over 700 people who joined us this afternoon for a town meeting in Cedar Rapids, Iowa to discuss the vital need for our government to boldly address the many crises facing working families in these troubling times. If we come together as a nation, I am confident we can not only solve the issues that we face, but we can also move this country forward in the fight for justice in its many forms.

node.text: Bernie stops at a local diner and starts an impromptu town hall on the reconciliation bill. Folks gather to ask questions - including former republicans.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Bernie Sanders in Detroit, Michigan. May be an image of 2 people, people sitting, people standing and outdoors.

node.text:
I very much appreciated spending time in Detroit today with Rep. @rashidatlaib, @repdingell, and @repandylevin as we spoke to the community on how our Budget Reconciliation Legislation will take an important step forward in the fight against climate change by making massive investments in wind, solar and other forms of renewable energy. Together, we can lead the world in transforming our energy systems away from fossil fuels.

📸: @detroitfreepress

node.text: I've said it before and I'll say it again: It is time for the Congress to finally have the guts to stand up to the wealthy and special interests, and restore the people's faith in the idea that our government can work for all of us.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Bernie Sanders on August 27, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'NOW IS THE TIME to invest in the needs of working people. PerniE tα BernieSanders.com'.

node.text:
For decades, the rich and corporations have had it pretty good. Good for them. Those days are over.

Now we are going to pass our Budget Reconciliation Legislation and finally help the poor, the working class, the seniors, and the children of this country.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Bernie Sanders on August 26, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'I understand that budget chairpersons historically, have done their work within the Beltway in D.C. I think really, the function of a budget chairman is to get out among the people. Sems_'.

node.text:
What you know, what I know, and truthfully, what Republicans know is that the ideas we are proposing under our Budget Reconciliation Legislation are enormously popular. Republicans know that the American people are sick and tired of the government working overtime for the wealthy, and the powerful, and they know that the American people want a government that works for all of us — and that's exactly why Republicans are a little nervous about our town halls tomorrow in Indiana and on Sunday in Iowa.

The contrast here is pretty clear — and we're going to win.

I very much look forward to speaking to working families in Indiana and Iowa this weekend.
